$AAPL  

Apple  is likely to beat Wall Street estimates for the December quarter, with services being a particular area of strength according to Morgan Stanley analyst Katy Huberty. 
However, Huberty said such gains have already been &quot;relatively priced in by the market.&quot; 

On Thursday, Huberty, who has an overweight rating and a $200-a-share price target on Apple&#39;s (AAPL) stock, said she expects Apple&#39;s (AAPL) services revenue for the quarter to total $19.2 billion, which is 3% ahead of Wall Street&#39;s estimates, and would represent a 21% increase from a year ago. Huberty said better-than-expected App Store performance is adding to Apple&#39;s (AAPL) services strength. 

Huberty said that Apple&#39;s (AAPL) revenue stability, upcoming product launches and expanding into new markets, such as the oft-rumored AR/VR headset &quot;makes [Apple] more defensive in a rising rate environment.&quot; 

